Build bullseye-lxde sdcard for Radxa rockpi4b:

Input files: ../rootfs-bullseye/linaro-rootfs.img
             ../rootfs-bullseye/linaro-esp.img

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD/EMMC to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
Eject NVME-SSD/sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD/EMMC from PC.

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD/EMMC to rockpi4b.
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo ifconfig
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sync
sudo shutdown -h now
Power off, power on
Disable power saving and screen saver.
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
date
Check if Debian is running UEFI mode:
ls /sys/firmware/efi

sudo apt install speedtest-cli build-essential libjpeg-dev libpng-dev libpng16-16 pkg-config libx11-dev python3-pip python3-setuptools chromium chromium-sandbox ffmpeg mpv git pandoc

speedtest-cli

git clone https://github.com/glmark2/glmark2.git -b 2021.02
cd glmark2
./waf configure --with-flavors=x11-glesv2
./waf
sudo ./waf install
glmark2-es2

